The '''400-Mile Yard Sale''', sometimes referred to as the '''Highway 68 Yard Sale''', is an outdoor [[second-hand]] sale held annually for four days, beginning in the first weekend of June. It takes place along [[U.S. Route 68 in Kentucky|U.S. Route 68]] (US&nbsp;68) in the US state of [[Kentucky]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.400mile.com/ |title=400-Mile Sale Across Kentucky Along Historic Hwy&nbsp;68 |publisher=400-Mile Sale |date= |access-date= June 18, 2015}}</ref> It is held in almost all areas along the US&nbsp;68 corridor from the east side of [[Paducah, Kentucky|Paducah]] through central Kentucky, and ending at [[Maysville, Kentucky|Maysville]].<ref name=400-milesale-locations>{{cite web|url=http://400mile.com/locations.html |title= Yard Sale Locations |publisher= 400-Mile Sale |date= |access-date= June 18, 2015}}</ref>
==History== In 2011, the 400-Mile Yard Sale route added [[Kentucky Route 80]] (KY&nbsp;80) from [[Aurora, Kentucky|Aurora]] to [[Murray, Kentucky|Murray]], in [[Calloway County, Kentucky|Calloway]] and [[Marshall County, Kentucky|Marshall]] counties in Kentucky.
Historically, the 400-mile sale boosts the economy of most localities along the route, most notably in [[Glasgow, Kentucky|Glasgow]], the county seat in [[Barren County, Kentucky|Barren County]], as that area has the highest economical impact annually, especially with the [[Glasgow Highland Games]] taking place during the same weekend as the sale.<ref name=gdt16>Perkins, Will (2016). [http://www.glasgowdailytimes.com/news/business-booms-in-glasgow-with-highland-games--mile-yard/article_e7dcae46-29df-11e6-b1fd-838e3226303f.html "Glasgow biz booms this weekend"]. Glasgow Daily Times, June 4, 2016, page A-1.</ref>
==Further information==
===Areas exempt from the event=== A {{convert|10|mi|km|adj=mid|-long}} stretch of the [[Concurrency (road)|concurrently running]] US&nbsp;68 and KY&nbsp;80 in the [[Land Between the Lakes National Recreation Area]] in western [[Trigg County, Kentucky|Trigg County]] is excluded from the yard sale route because the recreation area is the property of a government organization, the [[U.S. Forest Service]]. Another gap in the sale route, a {{convert|20|mi|km|adj=mid|long}} stretch of US&nbsp;68 in [[Lexington, Kentucky|Metropolitan Lexington]] and [[Fayette County, Kentucky|Fayette County]] is also excluded on account of high traffic volume, especially in downtown Lexington.<ref>{{cite book |title= 400-Mile Sale Brochure |year= 2013 |type= Pamphlet}}</ref>
===Events in the area=== A town-wide yard sale in the eastern [[Warren County, Kentucky|Warren County]] town of [[Smiths Grove, Kentucky|Smiths Grove]] is often held during the US&nbsp;68 Yard Sale just off the highway. [[Elkton, Kentucky|Elkton]], the [[Todd County, Kentucky|Todd County]] seat also has a lot of yard sales during the event, even if on other streets.<ref name=400-milesale-locations/><ref>{{cite web|date= April 15, 2015 |url=http://elktonky.com/events/400-mile-yard-sale/ |title=400-Mile Sale and Elkton Yard Sale Days |publisher= Elkton, Kentucky |access-date= June 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://elktonky.com/category/events/ |title= 400-Mile Sale and Elkton Yard Sale Days 2015 |publisher=Elkton, Kentucky |date= |access-date= June 18, 2015}}</ref> The [[Glasgow Highland Games]] at [[Barren River Lake State Resort Park]], well south of the US 68 corridor along [[US Route 31E]], is typically held during the same weekend as the 400 mile yard sale.<ref name=gdt16/>
==See also== *[[127 Corridor Sale]], the world's longest yard sale along [[U.S. Route 127|US&nbsp;127]] *[[Roller Coaster Fair]], held in October along [[Kentucky Route 63|KY&nbsp;63]] and [[Kentucky Route 90|KY&nbsp;90]]
